<item>
            <title>[CXF-7293] AbstractSpringComponentScanServer must ignore client proxy classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7293</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Follow-up to discussion: &lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/f0982d37f633ab831ecba95fda6b7e97c4b79d62f879914d495c9593@%3Cusers.cxf.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/f0982d37f633ab831ecba95fda6b7e97c4b79d62f879914d495c9593@%3Cusers.cxf.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In applications that expose some JAX-RS resources and use some&lt;br/&gt;
JAX-RS clients to access other systems, currently also these client proxies are exposed (if the application is configured with component-scan=true and classes-scan-packages). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll create a PR with a fix for it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
