&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 6c66f7477d32c05a27bd29101fe376a92b0e7398&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Dennis Kieselhorst &amp;lt;deki@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2017-03-21T15:48:57Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7293&quot; title=&quot;AbstractSpringComponentScanServer must ignore client proxy classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-7293&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-7293&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: AbstractSpringComponentScanServer must ignore client proxy classes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15934868" author="deki" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2017 16:48:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You mean instead of Proxy.class we should be more specific and use ClientProxyImpl?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like it makes sense to move this also to your newly introduced isValidComponent method, what do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15934886" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2017 16:57:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can&apos;t refer to the ClientProxyImpl because it is in the other module.&lt;br/&gt;
Can you use the newly added properties to make sure the client proxies are not included ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15934923" author="deki" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2017 17:21:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should work, I&apos;ll give it a try tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I still think it makes sense to ignore proxies by default because nobody is aware of that they get exposed automatically and this causes side-effects.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15934951" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2017 17:32:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But we don&apos;t want to lose the proxified service beans which can also happen, say if Spring transactions are enabled ? This is what I&apos;m concerned about.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15935961" author="deki" created="Wed, 22 Mar 2017 09:04:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a valid point. It also might happen in other scenarios e.g. when @Cacheable is used. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I modified the code, I don&apos;t like the classname String check, would be to have the class accessible but this would result in circular dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15945490" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Tue, 28 Mar 2017 16:33:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Dennis, thanks for the test (linked from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7291&quot; title=&quot;sharedPackageName for Swagger description should ignore proxy classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-7291&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-7291&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I did update AbstractSpringComponentScanServer though slightly differently from the proposed patch - to avoid losing the valid Spring-proxified service beans, though I&apos;m happy to count your patch as your next contribution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/cxf/commit/27ae9979&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/cxf/commit/27ae9979&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Sergey &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15945499" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 28 Mar 2017 16:35:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user asfgit closed the pull request at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/249&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/249&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
